answer.text: "If your not into drinking, I can see how you could easily miss this attraction but this is so much more than a drinker's version of paradise. If by now, you've fallen in love with Maui and how simple life seems out here, then you must come check out how Spirits are made with simple sugars! Yes, vodka made with Sugarcane!!! The people and the wandering roosters are friendly at this organic facility. The tour is short and sweet  (no pun intended.) The $10 tour will get you a sample too:) we didn't opt for the lunch since we found out it was a sack lunch. Oh, and the view from upcountry is magnificent. So, don't be that tourist who misses this attraction..yah!"
answer.ctaText: See more reviews for this business.

answer.text: "This is not one of those top Maui attractions or locations that any ordinary tourist (or resident) might visit, but Lahaina Animal Farm is an excellent place to meet and interact with the cows, donkeys, goats, sheep, pigs, turtles, tortoise, peacocks, and even rabbits and guinea pigs! The guides and staff really are passionate about animals and the history behind the Lahaina Animal Farm. Seeing and interacting with animals can really help with relieving stress and setting a good tone for the rest of the day. Daily guided farm tours offered from 9:00 AM - 11:30 AM."

answer.text: "Redline Rafting provides an open water snorkel adventure beyond compare. Sean and Chase were extremely friendly, knowledgeable, and helpful. They spent the day not only sharing information about the reef and history of Hawaii but also some knowledge about local attractions in Maui like Ho'okipa Beach to see the sea turtles come to the beach at sunset.   The trip is early - but you beat the crowds and it allows more time to see more of the amazing reef at Molokini Crater, including the back wall which is a must see. The raft is exciting and comfortable.   Had an excellent time and would recommend that anyone looking for a one of a kind snorkel trip go with Redline."
answer.ctaText: See more reviews for this business.

answer.text: "I go to Maui a lot, especially during whale season.  Ultimate Whale Watch is the only boat I go on now since I've had the best encounters from these safe, low to the water rafts.  The Humpbacks seem to be attracted to these yellow zodiacs more so then the larger cattle boats in my opinion.  My favorite Captains are Amy or Joel.  Both VERY good at following and staying with the whales from a safe distance but close enough to give everyone on board a great experience and most importantly not let the whales feel harassed or threatened.  There are several other "whale watch" boats that are there in Lahaina, but Ultimate is truly the ULTIMATE whale watch!   Here are some pics from this last weekend's 7:20am trip with Captain Amy."

answer.text: "We booked the Molokini crater snorkeling tour and we were really existing to see it. We started off towards it but then they turned back citing "rough waves". It seemed like a perfect day, great weather, so completely skipping this main attraction was a huge disappointment. They could have atleast shown the crater even if we couldn't snorkel there. The spot they took us to was very basic, some fishes but no turtles. Overall, wouldn't recommend this company if you really want some exciting snorkeling experience. And remember they might skip Molokini crater altogether, even if you pay for it, without providing any refunds!"
